Additionally, the paper involves probability distributions and matching them, which indicates that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions experiments involving image data, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it could belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions security and privacy concerns, which suggests that it could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
